The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and falls under the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) category. The paper also involves combinatorial structures and algorithms, which are relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The use of product distribution and the analysis of large rectangles suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.IT (Information Theory) category. The paper also involves discrete mathematics, which is relevant to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) category. Finally, the analysis of the combinatorial structure of search-like communication problems suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) category.
